One-Line Memory Trick

PEMDAS (Math rule):
Parentheses â†’ Exponents â†’ Multiplication/Division â†’ Addition/Subtraction
(Then comparisons, logical, assignment)

Quick Example : 

int x = 5 + 2 * 3 > 10 && 8 > 4;

Order :

2 * 3 = 6
5 + 6 = 11
11 > 10 â†’ true
8 > 4 â†’ true
true && true â†’ true

Final result: true
